<br>
Beka guided us out of the docking bay. I stood behind her with Drake standing next to me talking of medical procedures. His voice seemed to be grinding into my head like a drill and it took everything I had not to tell him to shut the hell up and stuff his procedure where the sun don’t shine. I knew taking my aggravation out on him wasn’t the answer.  I gazed at the stars and thought about the drugged engineer we had back in the bunks. I squeezed the railing until my knuckles were white with frustration and confusion. Harper was my friend and the best damn engineer I've ever seen.  I had no idea his past was full of such horrors and suffering. If I had known…What? What would I do? Would I have treated him differently? Was that what he was trying to avoid? I realized that his seemingly gregarious mood was probably a way of covering up the fact that mentally he was a wreck. These last few days have dredged up mixed feelings. One minute I would look in the mirror and become filled with rage and the next I would feel an over whelming sadness. What would I have done in his position? Probably the same thing. I’d probably would have hid it all behind a wall just like he did.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey Dylan, do you think it was a good idea to leave Tyr behind? He is the muscle…and if Harper goes ballistic were gonna need him.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I thought of that but Harper is well enough sedated that he won't cause a problem and in the slim chance that he might go crazy…I think an angry neitzchean is the last person you want to send after him. That is if you want him back alive.&quot; I said not realizing how breathy and tired I had sounded until I looked up to see Drake staring at me.<br>
<br>
&quot;ooo…that's true. And also Harper's been giving Tyr a run for his money lately&quot; Beka said looking back at me.  She also looked tired. I nodded thinking about how much it must torment Tyr that his bonespurs were broken off by a kludge. Over the 3 days Harper was confined to  med bay I’ve had to stop Tyr from entering medical eight times. I doubt if Tyr was trying to bring him a get well card. <br>
<br>
&quot;I'm gonna go back and check on Trance and Harper&quot; I said turning on my heel and sauntering off the bridge of the Maru. It felt strange being on this small ship. It was cozy yet cramped in a way and I felt the need to stretch out.  I walked smothered in my thoughts. My mind raced going over the procedure Blake had explained to me and going over the possibility that Harper's brain could hold the answer that could save the universe. I rubbed the bridge of my nose and kept walking. The Maru was small compared to Andromeda but the walk to the bunk room was surprisingly long. It gave me time to swallow my pride so I could talk to Harper like he was Harper the quirky engineer that I had respected and not the Harper that had beat me senseless less then a week ago. I rubbed my ribs in remembrance and winced a little. They were still sore and a few bruises were still visible on my chest. I was so surprised at the fact that he could be that malicious, that something inside him could be that malicious. Blake explained that Shane was a personification of Harper's most animalistic and deep seeded emotions but I wasn't sure if I could believe that. My ribs were my proof though and I should have known that growing up on the hellhole earth would have done some sort of irreparable damage to his psyche.  I sighed letting all the anger or resentment subside and letting myself be swallowed up by pity and empathy. The closer I got to my destination the more I thought I could feel his plight He had tried so hard to forget about his past, He tried to hid his feeling and doubt behind his mask and he tried to live a normal life. Even though he knew he had a monster rumbling inside of him who had done some insidious things. Blake had taken it upon himself to share with me some of the more intimate details of Harper's life on earth. The damage he had done and the fights he had caused and more then finished. Harper had become a terror in his camp at the age of 14 and he just couldn't help it. I turned the corner and prepared myself to enter the bunks and stare into the pleading and sorrowful blue eyes of the little guy that I felt an overwhelming need to protect.  He had become a son to me and I felt horrible not being able to recognize and fix his pain earlier.  The signs of his distress were there and I felt equally as horrible about loosing all control and threatening to kill the little man who inspired such a strong fatherly instinct within me. I always kept a watchful eye on him, studying his moods and reactions and trying to make life aboard the Andromeda comfortable for someone who had had to live the sort of life he had to. Making sure he wouldn't have to beg, steal, or fight for the necessities, but somehow I had neglected to notice what was important. I finally looked up after realizing that I had been walking with my head down dejectedly. The bunkroom's light was off with the exception of one over head light flickering ominously. I immediately drew my weapon. I had underestimated him the first time and I wasn't going to do it again. I walked forward slowly trying to make the least amount of noise possible. I twitched slightly every time my boots hit the grating. I looked around cautiously realizing that the maru was a very eerie place. The dark corners and equally dark nooks and crannies made my skin crawl and my breathing quicken.  I held on tight to my force lance. I didn't intend on shooting Harper, not after having this revelation on how much Harper means to me and this crew, but having this weapon in my hand made me feel more in control and at ease.  I made it to the door and looking into the jet-black room. I hesitated hoping my eyes would adjust but they didn't. I flashed back to how lightning fast and merciless Harper/Shane was and the fear of being injured doubled causing me to bite back a whimper. I was in the worst possible position. Knowing an enemy might be out to get us but not having the strength to hurt him. I wondered if it came down to if I could shoot Harper to defend this crew or myself. Could I kill him to protect this crew? I reached in the room and felt along the wall for the light switch.  I flipped it but nothing happened. <br>
<br>
“That’s just great.” I murmured. I looked around the room but I saw no one. <br>
<br>
“Trance?” I said easing into the room. All I could hear was the sound of one of the overhead lights flickering.  Click, clack, click clack. It had a strange rhythm to it that my heart felt like it had to match. It began to beat hard against my chest and I swallowed the lump that was stuck in my throat. What if he hurt Trance?<br>
<br>
“Trance?...Harper?” I said again finally making it to the middle of the room. The shadows that lingered in every corner turned my stomach and I was seriously afraid that lunch might come back to visit. The hair on the back of my neck stood on end and I heard a little scuffle which made me jump and whirl around frantically but I saw nothing. This whole scene reminded me of a horror vid I had seen which only heightened my fear.<br>
<br>
“Beka? Something strange is going on.”  I said pressing my neck communicator.<br>
<br>
“What Dylan?”<br>
<br>
“Trance and Harper are not in the bunks”<br>
<br>
“I’ll send Drake down and I’ll be there when I can. Beka out.” I nodded whipping the sweat from my upper lip. My eyes had grown tired from aimlessly shifting from dark corner to pitch black crevice. <br>
<br>
“Shane?” I said pulling at straws. The silence remained and I started to back out of the bunk room to look elsewhere.<br>
<br>
“You called?” Came a dark voice. His voice echoed off the wall and I whirled around again not sure where the voice had come from.<br>
<br>
“There’s an advantage to being little, I could be anywhere.” His voice was so different from Harper’s. Shane’s voice seemed to be deliberately spooky. It still had the child like ring to it but he whispered hauntingly. It felt like he was the little devil sitting on my shoulder whispering into my ear. I could here him breath slow and steady and I felt an urge to curl up in a ball and wait for my inevitable beating. That wouldn’t be a high guard response would it? But it wouldn’t be high guard either if I was forced to kill yet another crewmember. I flashed back to killing Rhade and my eyes watered despite myself.  My moment of reflection was cut short when I heard foot steps behind me. I cringed and squared my shoulders. I spun around and shot.<br>
<br>
“HEY! WHAT THE HELL!”<br>
<br>
“Oh…ummm…sorry Drake. I thought you were someone else.”<br>
<br>
“SHIT!” He said still reeling from the fact that I’d almost shot him. He stomped around in a circled with both anger and shock on his face.  I heard hurried footsteps in the distance. Me and drake looked at each other and I watched his pupils expand in fear. He pulled his gauss gun and I gripped my force lance and we both followed the sound. The footsteps were short and choppy like a childs. <br>
<br>
“Shane…We are trying to help you.” I said walking slowly. I needed to pee badly and the fear only exaggerated the need. Drake’s strides matched mine and he walked slightly hunched over, grabbing the area where his wound use to be. I could see the worry on his face. The thought of being shot again scared the hell out of him.<br>
<br>
“There is no need to try to reason with him. He won’t listen” Drake whispered.<br>
<br>
“Dylan!” I heard a weak scream and my instincts told me to run and get there as fast as I could but my training told me it was a trap. Drake stared at me for guidance. <br>
<br>
“You know it’s a trap right?” He said pleadingly. He knew I would go anyway.<br>
<br>
“I know…But we can’t leave Trance with him.” I said. I breathed in deep and ran hearing Drake’s footsteps pick up a few seconds later. I slowly climbed down the ladder into the engine room. Harper had picked this location because weapons fire in here would be suicide. I looked around at the horrible lighting and slowed my decent in utter fear.  I would have rathesr fight maggog then my own crew member.  A lump wiggled at the far end of the ramp and I quickly made my way over to it. <br>
<br>
“Trance? Are you alright?” I said turning her over. Physically she seemed ok but her eyes kept rolling back in her head an her mouth was taped shut. All my attention was on her and I didn’t notice the shadow hovering above. <br>
<br>
“Dylan look out!” I looked back at Drake who was pointing up at the ceiling. I looked up just in time to have a falling fist hit me square in my nose. I stumbled back and heard Drakes gauss gun power up. <br>
<br>
“Don’t shoot! Not in the engine room!” I yelled stepping back from Harper rubbing my bloodied nose. Harper knelt down and sat trance up ripping the tape away from her mouth. Her head bobbed and her mouth hung open.<br>
<br>
“She reminds me of me. You know when you gave me all those pills to swallow.” He said reaching into his pocket. He pulled out an assortment of pills.<br>
<br>
“I’ve been saving them just for her, making Harper pocket a few here and there. Harper calls them paradise…who better to give them to then a purple pixie.” He said stuffing a few more down her throat. She gagged in response but swallowed them. <br>
<br>
“Harper! How many have you given her!” I yelled. From the looks of it she was ODing and needed medical attention at once.<br>
<br>
“I’m not Harper!” He stomped and balled his fist. His eyes were as big as saucers and all the mucles in his face and neck were tight with anger.<br>
<br>
“ok, ok…calm down…you’re not Harper I’m sorry. Just please let Trance go.”<br>
<br>
“I can’t I promised Harper I’d show her a good time.” He licked the side of her face. Trance looked so helpless. If her eyes hadn’t been moving I would have thought she were dead. Her tailed flopped randomly like a dieing fish. I teared up just watching her slowly die before my eyes. <br>
<br>
“Shane…” A voice came from behind me. I dared to tear my attention away from Harper and look behind me to see Beka standing authoritatively.<br>
<br>
“Let trance go!” She said stepping forward. I looked back at Shane who seemed confused. He looked around and started to shake.<br>
<br>
“Mom?” He said with both fear and hope in his voice. <br>
<br>
“Let trance go and come here and give me a hug.” Beka said sweetly but her fear was evident. I wasn’t sure what was going on but it was working. <br>
<br>
“I’m sorry I hit you and called you names. You know how I get sometimes.” He said sadly. He seemed totally different now.<br>
<br>
“Please don’t be mad at me…I promise I won’t do it again.” He tugged at his shirt and dropped the remaining pills. His face balled up like he was gonna cry. He looked pitiful.<br>
<br>
“I know I forgive you. Just come here.” He walked slowly past me toward Beka who was greeting him with open arms. She smiled brightly and so did Shane and for a second I could see Harper.<br>
<br>
“Careful Beka…” Drake said and dramatically Shane’s face changed. It was like a storm had rolled in quickly. Her name had triggered something.<br>
<br>
“Beka!” he said loudly balling his fist up and looking at her from underneath his lashes.<br>
<br>
“Shit!” beka cried. She started to step back and I grabbed Shane from behind. He quickly elbowed my in my face making my already broken nose gush even more blood. I hobbled back and he tackled Beka to the ground.<br>
<br>
“LIAR!” He screamed. Pummeling her with blow after blow. Drake stood modified. He dropped his gun and scurried to the ladder like the coward I thought he was. <br>
<br>
“Shane please!” Beka said and he stopped and got up with hesitation. <br>
<br>
“You thought you could get inside my head and mix everything all up.” He said throwing his hands around in a psychotic fit. I held my nose and watched through my tear filled eyes. I felt dizzy and disoriented while the blood coated my hands. He didn’t seem like the same cocky Shane. Something was different. He thought of Beka as his mother? I was confused. Beka groaned rolling around restlessly on the ground. Shane pointed at her.<br>
<br>
“I didn’t do that…She deserved it. I…I didn’t do that.” His voice trailed off and he began to run. He picked up the weapon Drake had dropped and began to climb the ladder. <br>
<br>
“I locked the controls Shane. You won’t get anywhere.” Beka said with a course voice. <br>
<br>
“Why…Why would you do that! Why are you hurting me!” He said in frustrating. The kind or utter frustration that makes you cry loudly. <br>
<br>
“I’m not hurting you I’m helping you.” Beka said sadly laying flat on her back. She coughed and wiped the blood from her nose.<br>
<br>
“No, NO! You’re hurting me mom!” He said pleadingly. He climbed down from the latter and pointed the gun at her. Beka sat up wearily and once again extended her arms.<br>
<br>
“Come here…”<br>
<br>
“NO!” He screamed powering the gauss gun up and shaking with insanity. A battle was being fought inside of him and Shane was losing.<br>
<br>
“Come here!” Beka yelled sternly. Shane snapped into submission. Like a child who feared getting a spanking. He knelt down in front of Beka and sat with his back to her. She rubbed his back and rocked him slowly taking the gun from his hand and handing it to me slyly. Ever second that went by seemed to dull the rage on his face. Beka whispered to him and he nodded. She ran her fingers through his hair and I watched a tear slide down his cheek. I saw a flicker from above a looked up to see Drake. A spark of hate flashed in my heart but then he held up the dart gun he had gotten from weapons storage. I nodded and in one swift movement he tossed it to me, I caught it and before Harper could react I shot him square in his chest. He wiggled against Beka but she started to sing and he stopped resisting and slumped against her. <br>
<br>
“This reminds me of something…” he slurred.<br>
<br>
“Hush little baby don’t say a word…” She continued and his eyes drooped and fell. Beka continued to rock him until he fell limp in her arms then she cried helplessly into his hair rocking him mournfully.<br>
<br>
The scene was so utterly heart breaking that I cried openly and I realized in a way she was his mother…She had been his mother ever since she had taken him from earth. She had clothed, fed and taught him everything she knew. She was there when he was sick…When he cried and when he laughed. I walked up to her and let her morn for her son and like any mother I knew she would give anything to fix his damage...<br>
<br>
<br>
To Be Continued…<br>
<br>
*sniff* there's something in my eye....<br>
